        <h3>Bio</h3>
        <p><span itemprop="author">Sascha Zyroslaw Kyrill Manns</span> is a programmer, author and supporter in Germany. He worked inside the <a href="https://connect.opensuse.org/pg/profile/saigkill" target="_blank">openSUSE Community</a> as <a href="https://build.opensuse.org/user/show/saigkill" target="_blank">packager</a>, <a href="https://news.opensuse.org/tag/newsletter/" target="_blank">weekly news editor</a>, the board election team and the membership reviewing team. For the open-slx GmbH he worked on the openSUSE Box and wrotes handbooks and tutorials and gives support for that distribution. </p>
        <p>He founded a openSUSE based distribution for doctors and hospitals, which provides many open source software for the medical context. It targets people in poor contries which can't buy expensive proprietary tools.</p>
        <p>After leaving open-slx he worked as Dispatcher, Author for Process-Management, as programmer for business workflow apps and websites and as programmer for Cache databases.</p>
        <p>Sascha studied economic computer science, is Specialist Application Development, learned to program in Ruby, Python, JavaScript, C# and finished a SCRUM-Master course.</p>
